There were [no significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/96a5696e-0d20-4278-b872-e53c1487cd8d/to/b67bbf30-cf8f-4dc8-b4b5-c1df0841a36f) against commit e19c07e6753d1d2844a1849a0077a6c9ad2d8676.
!bench

Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/de743294-2469-44e4-b8db-8fd8dc9db518) for commit ff2aee382d03cfdc532bc2452700654be611ce76.
There were [no significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/96a5696e-0d20-4278-b872-e53c1487cd8d/to/de743294-2469-44e4-b8db-8fd8dc9db518) against commit e19c07e6753d1d2844a1849a0077a6c9ad2d8676.

General information: ```text build: -8.3062 * 10‚Åπ (-0.00676%) ``` 1 file got slower by at least 10‚Åπ instructions: ```text Mathlib.Geometry.RingedSpace.PresheafedSpace.Gluing: +1.4055 * 10‚Åπ (+0.347%) ``` No file got slower by at least 10%. 5 files got faster by at least 10‚Åπ instructions: ```text Mathlib.Analysis.NormedSpace.PiTensorProduct.InjectiveSeminorm: -3.5123 * 10‚Åπ (-1.21%) Mathlib.Topology.Category.TopCat.Limits.Pullbacks: -1.6817 * 10‚Åπ (-4.16%) Mathlib.Topology.Algebra.Field: -1.5747 * 10‚Åπ (-13.5%) Mathlib.Geometry.RingedSpace.OpenImmersion: -1.5114 * 10‚Åπ (-0.804%) Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Category.Cat.Limit: -1.4023 * 10‚Åπ (-1.37%) ``` 1 files got faster by at least 10%: ```text Mathlib.Topology.Algebra.Field: -13.5% ```
See also #13994, which does this differently (your choice might be better!) and goes further.
#13994 gives a speed-up nearly ten times as large.
As I mentioned in #13994, we should not be addin `fun_prop` as default values until #11092 is finished. I'm adding that as a dependency.
@j-loreaux I reverted the `:= by ...` parts of this PR to avoid conflicts with @grunweg 's work. Now it's just +3 `@[fun_prop]` attrs.

Looking at the bench, the increase in `dsimp` time is greater than the decrease in `aesop` time. I don't know what's the right choice here. Without `dsimp`, it looks at goals like `Continuous (Equiv.mk ..).invFun` and can't proceed.

```suggestion
  continuous_toFun : Continuous toFun := by continuity
```

```suggestion
  continuous_invFun : Continuous invFun := by continuity
```
